    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> diuina
                        fauente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si iustis uenerabilium
                        locorum diuino cultui mancipatis episcopatibus munus quodlibet nostrae
                        dapsilitats conferimus, premia sine fine mansura, Domino largiente,
                        percipere non ambigimus. Quapropter omnium fidelium sanctae Dei ecclesiae
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet et futurorum nouerit industria, quoniam <rs
                            key="#Intercessory">interuentu ac petitione</rs>
                        <persName key="#Intercessory #Consiliarius_regis #Bishops" ref="#people/220"
                            >Zenobii</persName> uenerabilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et
                        dilecti <rs key="#Consiliarius_regis">consiliarii nostri</rs> concessimus et
                        condonauimus <orgName key="#Landed_possessions #Mother_churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/204">ecclesiae Sanctorum Ioannis et
                            Miniati</orgName>, que caput est <placeName ref="#places/2"
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Mother_churches #Bishops"
                            >Florentini</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Mother_churches">episcopatus</rs>, cui auctore Deo <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/271">Grasulfus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> preesse uidetur, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object">terram</rs> uidelicet
                        ad <rs key="#Size">modios duodecim</rs>, quae dicitur <placeName
                            ref="#places/522"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Emperor/king"
                            >Campus <rs key="#Emperor/king">Regis</rs></placeName>, prope ipsam
                        ecclesiam Beati Ioannis positam, hactenus pertinentem de <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#estates/159"><rs
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential">curte</rs>
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">Regis</rs></geogName> sita Florentiae et ita <rs
                            key="#Confinia">determinatam</rs>: de duabus partibus terra ipsius
                        ecclesiae, ex tertia parte percurrit <rs key="#Confinia #Rivers">fluuius
                            Munione</rs>, de quarta uero parte terra <persName
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Consortes/shared_possessions"><name
                                ref="Magibertus">Magiberti</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Consortes/shared_possessions"><name
                                ref="Morbertus">Mauriperti</name></persName> ac <persName
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Consortes/shared_possessions"><name
                                ref="Florebertus">Floriberti</name></persName> eourmque <rs
                            key="#Consortes/shared_possessions">consortium</rs>. Aliam quoque <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Fiscal_property #Object">petiam terrae</rs> ad <rs
                            key="#Size">modios sex</rs>, hactenus pertinentem de <geogName
                            ref="#estates/233" key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential"
                                ><rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> Beneuentana</geogName>, positam prope
                            <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/205">Sancti Miniati</orgName>, et est ipsa terra
                            <rs key="#Confinia">circumdata de omni parte</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/523"
                            key="#Petiae #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                ><rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> Beati Miniati</placeName>,
                        in cuius ecclesia sanctorum corpora octo quiescunt, de nostro iure et
                        potestate praedictam terram, sicut superius legitur, cum suis
                        terminationibus in ius et potestatem ipsius ecclesiae modis omnibus
                        transfundimus et perdonamus, ut presul ipsius ecclesiae habeat, teneat atque
                        possideat potestatemque habeat ad honorem iam dicti episcopatus donandi,
                        uendendi, commutandi, seu mancipiandi, remota totius potestatis
                        inquietudine. Si quis igitur, quod minime credimus, contra hoc nostrae
                        concessionis praeceptum insurgere temptauerit, sciat se compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras triginta</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >medietatem palatio nostro</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem parti eiusdem
                            ecclesiae</rs>. Ut autem uerius credatur et diligentius ab omnibus
                        obseruetur, manu propria roboratum anulo nostro subter iussimus sigillari.
                        Signum (M) domni Berengarii gloriosissimi regis. <persName key="#Notary"
                                ><name ref="Martianus">Martianus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> ad uicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/58">Petri</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognoui et subscripsi. (SR) Data VII kalendas
                        maii, anno incarnationis Domini DCCCXCVIII, domni autem Berengarii
                        gloriosissimi regis XII, indictione II. Actum <placeName ref="#places/65"
                            >Papiae</placeName>. In Dei nomine feliciter; amen.</ab>
                </div>
